cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CC 

This paper deals with the task of measuring time with spiking neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and their applications (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of compressed counting networks, which relates to information theory (cs.IT). The construction of the neural timer involves probabilistic analysis, which is a common topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the synchronization of neural networks, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the design and analysis of circuits, which is a topic in computer engineering (cs.CC).
